Sentencas: Anode-supported, micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells were prepared and operated, utilizing mixed-reactant (methane and air mixture) supply.
Titulo: Mixed-reactant, micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells: An experimental study

Sentencas: The cells were composed of conventional materials, i.e. nickel, yttria-stabilized zirconia (Ni-YSZ) as anode supported Material, yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) as electrolyte, and lanthanum strontium manganite (LSM) as cathode material.
Titulo: Mixed-reactant, micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells: An experimental study

Sentencas: The cells were operated at various temperatures in between 550 and 800 degrees C with varying methane/air ratio (1:1-1:4.76).
Titulo: Mixed-reactant, micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells: An experimental study

Sentencas: Cell performance Was found to be strongly dependent on flow Fate and mixing ratio.
Titulo: Mixed-reactant, micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells: An experimental study

Sentencas: At 750 degrees C, the maximum open circuit voltage (OCV) of the cell was 1.05 V at a methane/air ratio of 1:4.76, with a maximum power output of 122 mW cm(-2).
Titulo: Mixed-reactant, micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells: An experimental study

Sentencas: The degradation test shows 0.05% performance loss per 24h, thereafter, fluctuations in current density were observed clue to oxidation-reduction cycles over nickel surface.
Titulo: Mixed-reactant, micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells: An experimental study

Sentencas: It is therefore concluded that although the methane/air ratio of 1:4.76 gives the best performance but the long-term performance is not guaranteed under Such conditions.
Titulo: Mixed-reactant, micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells: An experimental study
